Derived code and attribution
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

mchord is part of the *mpump* family of local-first browser instruments by the
same author. All sibling projects are licensed AGPL-3.0-or-later, and the code
reused here is reused under AGPL-3.0-or-later with attribution within the same
author and suite. The following portions are derived from sibling projects:

* Build tooling, the PWA service worker + precache strategy, and the
  Vite / TypeScript / ESLint configuration patterns — derived from **mgrains**.

* The Ableton Link bridge client and clock math (src/transport/link.ts and
  related) — derived from **mdrone** / **mpump** (linkBridge.ts, linkClock.ts).

* The Web MIDI router, note-ownership tracking, and MIDI message parsing
  (src/midi/) — derived from **mpumpit**.

* The defensive persistence layer and the share-link codec patterns
  (src/persistence/, src/sharing/) — derived from **mgrains** and **mloop**.

* The Web Audio sound engine (src/audio/) — derived from **mdrone** and
  **mgrains**. Specifically: the master-bus chain blueprint, the gentle
  glue-compressor settings + safe gain staging, the AnalyserNode output-meter
  tap, the preset-change "duck" to mask reconfiguration artefacts, the
  procedural reverb-IR generator, and the voice-pool / ADSR-VCA / click-free
  AudioParam-ramp approach — from **mdrone** (src/engine/MasterBus.ts). The
  module-scope singleton + `import.meta.hot` HMR-dispose lifecycle — from
  **mdrone** (src/App.tsx). The AudioWorklet `?worker&url` + `addModule`
  loading convention, the AudioWorkletProcessor ambient-type declarations, and
  the AudioContext resume / iOS-interruption handling — from **mgrains**
  (src/audio/AudioEngine.ts, src/audio/granular.worklet.ts). The mchord
  look-ahead limiter worklet (src/audio/worklets/limiter.worklet.ts) is new.

These derivations were confirmed by the suite lead. Because every source project
is AGPL-3.0-or-later by the same author, the reuse is covered by that license;
this NOTICE records the lineage for attribution and transparency.
